sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend (React)
    participant A as API Server (Django)
    participant DB as Database

    U->>F: Open app and navigate to login
    F->>U: Display login form
    U->>F: Enter credentials
    F->>A: POST /api/auth/login/ (username, password)
    A->>DB: Query user credentials
    DB-->>A: User data
    A->>A: Validate password, generate JWT tokens
    A-->>F: Return access & refresh tokens
    F->>F: Store tokens in localStorage
    F-->>U: Redirect to dashboard

    U->>F: Browse products
    F->>A: GET /api/products/items/
    A->>DB: Query products
    DB-->>A: Product list
    A-->>F: Return products
    F-->>U: Display products

    U->>F: Select product for subscription
    F->>U: Show subscription form
    U->>F: Enter subscription details
    F->>A: POST /api/subscriptions/ (product_id, schedule, etc.)
    A->>DB: Insert subscription record
    DB-->>A: Confirmation
    A-->>F: Return subscription data
    F-->>U: Show success message

    Note over U,F: Optional: Payment if required
    U->>F: Proceed to payment
    F->>A: POST /api/payments/ (amount, method)
    A->>DB: Create payment record
    DB-->>A: Payment ID
    A-->>F: Return payment details
    F-->>U: Display payment confirmation